## Plan Summary

**Only `common/chat.cpp` needs to be modified** — two additions. `common/chat.h` is untouched since `COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY` already exists.

### Step 1: New handler function
Insert after line 1517 (end of `common_chat_params_init_gigachat_v3`), before `namespace workaround {`:

```cpp
static common_chat_params common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(
        const common_chat_template & tmpl, const autoparser::generation_params & inputs) {
    (void) tmpl;
    common_chat_params data;
    std::string system_prompt;
    bool first_user = true;

    for (const auto & msg : inputs.messages) {
        const auto role    = msg.value("role", "");
        const auto content = msg.value("content", "");

        if (role == "system") {
            system_prompt = content;
        } else if (role == "user") {
            if (first_user) {
                data.prompt += "[INST] ";
                if (!system_prompt.empty()) {
                    data.prompt += system_prompt + "\n";
                }
                data.prompt += content + " [/INST]";
                first_user = false;
            } else {
                data.prompt += "[INST] " + content + " [/INST]";
            }
        } else if (role == "assistant") {
            data.prompt += " " + content + "</s>";
        }
    }

    data.format = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY;
    return data;
}
```

This produces:
- With system: `[INST] {system}\n{user1} [/INST] {assistant1}</s>[INST] {user2} [/INST]`
- Without system: `[INST] {user1} [/INST] {assistant1}</s>[INST] {user2} [/INST]`

(`<s>` BOS is handled by the tokenizer, not in `data.prompt`.)

### Step 2: Detection logic
Insert between the GigaChatV3 detection block (line 1688) and `return std::nullopt` (line 1690):

```cpp
    // Mistral Instruct v0.3 - uses [INST]/[/INST] markers without [SYSTEM_PROMPT]
    // [SYSTEM_PROMPT] presence distinguishes Ministral 3 (already handled above)
    if (src.find("[INST]") != std::string::npos &&
        src.find("[/INST]") != std::string::npos &&
        src.find("[SYSTEM_PROMPT]") == std::string::npos) {
        LOG_DBG("Using specialized template: Mistral Instruct v3\n");
        return common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(tmpl, params);
    }
```

The negative `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` check is the key safety mechanism: Ministral 3's template contains `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]`, so it's already matched earlier in `common_chat_try_specialized_template()` and will never reach this new check.
